BLOCK 1 — Create pei_ruleversion table + primary column
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

WHERE: make.powerapps.com → dev environment → Tables → + New table
       → "Set advanced properties" (use the full dialog, NOT quick "New table")

─── PROPERTIES PANE ───────────────────────────────────────────────

Display name:        Rule Version
Plural name:         Rule Versions
Schema name:         pei_ruleversion
                     (publisher prefix pei_ should lock in from the
                      solution; verify the rest reads exactly
                      "ruleversion" — no caps, no underscores)

Description:
Immutable per-Activate snapshot of a Rule. One row per (Rule, Version Number) pair. Stores the Conditions JSON and Output that were in effect at the moment the version was activated. Cycles pin to a specific Rule Version row (per ADR-054) to make 'what did this rule say when this cycle ran' answerable for the life of the platform.

Ownership:           User or team
Enable attachments:  OFF
Enable mobile offline: OFF
Enable notes:        ON
Enable activities:   OFF
Enable Quick Create form: OFF   ← ★ AC requirement, must be off
Track changes (audit): ON  (if shown here; else we set it at Block 5)


─── PRIMARY COLUMN TAB ───  ★ SET BEFORE FIRST SAVE  ★ ───────────

Display name:        Version Label
Schema name:         pei_versionlabel
                     ← verify this reads EXACTLY pei_versionlabel
                       (lowercase L, no "New_column" fallback,
                       no "VersionLabel" with caps)
Data type:           Single line of text
Format:              Text
Maximum length:      200
Required:            Required (business required)
Searchable:          Yes


─── PRE-SAVE CHECKLIST ───  verify all three BEFORE clicking Save:

  [ ] Properties: schema name = pei_ruleversion
  [ ] Properties: Quick Create form = OFF
  [ ] Primary column: schema = pei_versionlabel  ← the B01 trap

Then click Save. Wait ~10-30s for provisioning to complete.

